Type Parameters:

O - The Ordinate type
P - The type of the data point

All Known Implementing Classes:
LinkedListSeries, OHLCTimeSeries, OHLCVirtualTimeSeries, TickTimeSeries, TimeSeries
public interface ISeries<A extends Comparable<A>,O extends Comparable<O>,P extends ISeriesPoint<A,O>>
extends Iterable<P>, IPersistentIdentifiable

Read-only time series, the main collection type in the framework. Implementors must be thread-safe. Size and iterators must be snapshots. Listeners are notified on a best-effort basis. Depending on the value returned by isEnforceStrictSequence(), a series will allow more than one data-point for the same abscissa, or not.

isEnforceStrictSequence

boolean isEnforceStrictSequence()
A series can enforce the strict sequence of data-points, in which case it will never have more than one data-point for a specific abscissa; or be more lenient, depending on the value of this method

Returns:
true if the series does not allow more than one data-point for each abscissa, false if it does
